This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new unsupervised node representation learning approach based on mutual information maximization. It also involves the use of deep learning methods to address the challenges of spatio-temporal graphs. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of a model that can learn and encode relevant information about the input graph. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it deals with the analysis of spatio-temporal graphs such as traffic networks. 

It could also be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it involves the study of the dynamics of graphs over time. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of deep learning methods to address the challenges of spatio-temporal graphs.
